{
  "article_id": "TheMorningCall1893",
  "paragraphs": [
    [
      {
        "text": "The steam-schooner ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Jennie Griffin",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "sh_jennie",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "arrived this morning from ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicolas Island",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Captain Mullett",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "jmu",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "and crew tell of strange and wonderful meteorological disturbances on ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "The schooner",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "sh_jennie",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "is engaged in the crawfish business for ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the Pacific Coast Fishing and Packing Company",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "paccoastfishing",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "of ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "this city",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "ci_sd",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", and a couple of weeks ago left a gang of eight men on ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicolas",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "to prosecute the work.",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "The ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Jennie Griffin",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "sh_jennie",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "arrived there last Sunday to load the catch for this point, but received news instead which astounded the whole party, and caused ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Captain Mullett",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "jmu",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "to take on the gang from shore and leave ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "as quickly as he could.",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "The men reported that ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "had been visited by a tremendous gale of wind which raised the sea in the nature of a tidal wave, completely filling with sand the only harbor of ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", which is marked \"",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Coral harbor",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "re_coralharbor",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "\" on the Government charts. ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Captain Mullett",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "jmu",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "was dumfounded to find a stretch of sand where two weeks ago he rode at anchor in ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "his schooner",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "sh_jennie",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": ". A big crawfish car holding about five tons of fish, which was moored in the bay, was half-covered with sand and the fish were lost.",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "The foreman on shore kept a logbook, which was seen by ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "THE CALL",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "morningcall",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "correspondent. In it is recorded everything occurring from the date of the arrival of the men until July 2. The weather for several days was most remarkable. Everything seemed to foretell disaster. Seabirds and other living things acted strangely. On June 26 at 11 A. M. a heavy earthquake was experienced on ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". The oscillation was from east to west, the shocks being of several seconds' duration. ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "The Kanakas",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "natam_hawaiian",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "and one negro [sic] in a separate camp were scared almost to death and became almost crazy, running up and down in terror.",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "The weather was then very foggy with stifling heat. A peculiar light covered the sea in spite of the fog, adding a weird aspect to the scene. So far as the men could tell the fog centered about ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". Next day a tremendous wind-storm arose, causing great damage. No attempt was made by the men to work. All expected ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "to sink in the sea at any moment.",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "On June ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "[...]",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "earthquake ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "[...]",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "was heavy ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "[...]",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "over ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the is",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "[...]",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "men obser",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "[...]",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "a few yard",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "[...]",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "transparency of ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "[...]",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "see for quite a distance, and ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Captain Mullett",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "jmu",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "thinks the steamer's compasses were affected by the strange occurrences and the accompanying electrical disturbance. The ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Jennie Griffin",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "sh_jennie",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "was in the neighborhood in the fog and her two compasses would not work together while near ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". The men could not make out the name of ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the steamer",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "sh_jennie",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": ", which finally stood away from ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ".",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Still another distinct shock of earthquake was felt at noon on June 30, the vibrations being from east to west. This completed the demoralization of the camp, and the logbook says the men became howling savages.",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "A remarkable incident connected with the phenomena is that crawfish and other fish died from some unknown cause, probably electricity, as the men remembered afterward seeing lights on the water at night.",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "When the ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Jennie Griffin",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "sh_jennie",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "hove in sight the men waded out to meet the small boats, refusing to return to ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the land",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Captain Mullett",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "jmu",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "refused to believe their story, but was finally compelled to accept the foreman's word. All the men were taken on board ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the schooner",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "sh_jennie",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": ", which hastily sailed away.",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "San Nicolas",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "is the most westerly of the group known as ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the Santa Barbara Islands",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "and is about 150 miles from ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "San Diego",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "ci_sd",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". Twenty-five years ago it was covered with grass, which afforded pasture for thousands of sheep, whose owner lived there in a fine residence. A strange transformation has been going since then.",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "It is now a windy, barren, sandy waste, where but a few hundred sheep without a shepherd eke out a miserable existence. It is but eight miles long and four wide, but wherever one digs can be found human bones and skulls. In the distant past it must have been rather densely populated, or may have been the site of a burial-ground or a battle-field.",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Some fifty years ago ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the last inhabitant",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "was found in the person of a woman. ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "A Santa Barbara otter-hunter",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "named Nidever found her and took her to his home, where she died shortly after without being able to make any one understand her language. She was found in a cave, subsisting on fish caught with hooks made of abalone shells. Her discovery caused considerable interest in the scientific world at the time.",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      }
    ]
  ]
}